function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1]), words)
end

# test
@assert keep_only_names(["Apple", "banana", "Carrot", "dog"]) == ["Apple", "Carrot"]
```

The function `keep_only_names` is defined to filter the list of words based on whether the first character of each word is uppercase or not. The `filter` function is used with a condition that checks if the first character of the word is uppercase using the `isuppercase` function. The function returns the filtered list of words.

The function is then tested with the provided data. The expected output is `["Apple", "Carrot"]`, which the function correctly produces.
